programme.title: Human Dart
programme.desc: A skydiver goes high and long to set the world record for the farthest absolute distance flown in a wingsuit. Skydiver Andy Stumpf loves a challenge, so when he has the opportunity to break four world records in one shot, he jumps at the chance. But what he wants above all else is to break the record for the farthest absolute distance flown in a wingsuit.

programme.title: Mojave test pilot
programme.desc: Test pilot Elliot Seguin must decide if he should build and fly an experimental plane as an expectant father. Test pilot Elliot Seguin has always dreamed of building and flying his own experimental aircraft. His Quickie design is on the verge of completion, but when Elliot finds out he's going to be a father, he must decide if the risk is worth the reward.

programme.title: ABC of... Formula One
programme.desc: Get a crash course in F1 racing, with lessons in the terminology, history, heroes and drama of the sport. Find out everything you need to know about the international motorsport of Formula One racing with facts and figures, as well as lessons in the terminology, disciplines, history, heroes, and drama of the sport.

programme.title: One Track Back
programme.desc: Follow Matthias Walkner through a journey of rehab and redemption as he overcomes injury and returns to form. Matthias Walkner, the daredevil in the world of rally raid biking, made the impossible possible: after a heavy crash at the 2016 Dakar Rally, sidelining his career, he gets crowned Dakar Rally champion only two years later.

programme.title: Mad Mike's drifting Lamborghini NIMBUL races KAMAZ to Goodwood
programme.desc: 'Mad' Mike and Eduard Nikolaev tear up the Goodwood estate in the race to make it the Festival of Speed. The Goodwood Festival of Speed is here, and in the race to arrive at the annual ball in style and bag the last parking space 'Mad' Mike Whiddett and Eduard Nikolaev cause country estate havoc.

programme.title: Cowboy Boots
programme.desc: An American style that now spans the globe, Kyle Ng digs his heels in to learn about the cowboy boot. Saddle up and join Kyle Ng as he travels the world to learn how the cowboy boot made its way off the prairie. He visits Texas, United States to see where it all began, chills with cowboys in Rome, Italy, and rocks out with Kenyan heavy metal cowboys.

programme.title: King of the Mountain
programme.desc: Brandon Semenuk and the crew arrive in France to compete at the muddy Châtel Mountain Style FMB event. Brandon Semenuk and the crew go to France to compete at the Châtel Mountain Style freeride mountain bike event. Despite a plague of injuries and muddy conditions, Brandon takes on the gnarly course before having fun on the world’s longest zip line.

programme.title: Les 2 Alpes Bike Park
programme.desc: During a competition-filled month, Brandon Semenuk goes to France for a Crankworx event at Les 2 Alpes. In the midst of a competition-filled month, Brandon Semenuk travels to France for a Crankworx event at Les 2 Alpes. Due to unforeseen weather conditions, he has one chance to nail a perfect run if he wants to make it to the top of the podium.

programme.title: Bearclaw Invitational
programme.desc: Brandon Semenuk looks to stay undefeated on the year at a slopestyle event on Vancouver Island, Canada. Brandon Semenuk looks to stay undefeated on the year at Bearclaw Invitational, a slopestyle event on Vancouver Island, BC, Canada. Then, to avoid burnout from the gruelling schedule, he gets off his bike to take a supercharged go-kart for a spin.

programme.title: Florence
programme.desc: Adam Trent is off to Florence, Italy, to see authentic Italian culture in the birthplace of the Renaissance. After experiencing the lifestyle of the rich and famous in Monaco, Adam Trent is off to Florence, Italy, to immerse himself in authentic Italian culture. The connections he makes with his magic unlock secrets of the city known only to the locals.

programme.title: Blast Off
programme.desc: Aiden Glasby and Daryl Clarke embark on an adventure across Australia with modest microlight equipment. Aiden Glasby and Daryl Clarke embark on an ambitious adventure across Australia with a pair of modest microlight aircrafts. Accompanied by their fiancées, Lexi and Elsie, and a local guide, Bart, they fly to their first stop: Wardang Island.

programme.title: Locked In
programme.sub-title: First descent of the Beriman Gorge
programme.desc: Ben Stookesberry and a group of kayakers attempt a first descent of the Beriman River in Papua New Guinea. Ben Stookesberry and a group of professional kayakers journey to the remote jungles of Papua New Guinea to attempt a first descent of the Beriman River, a daunting 40km run lined with sheer limestone walls and no way out but to ride to the ocean.

programme.title: Iron to the Core
programme.desc: Long-distance triathlete Sebastian Kienle gives an inside look at what it takes to be an IRONMAN athlete. Decorated long-distance triathlete Sebastian Kienle gives an inside look at what it takes to be an IRONMAN athlete. From preparation to race day, it's a life spent enduring gruelling trials, but every small success makes the arduous journey worth it.

programme.title: AWOLNATION – Kill Your Heroes
programme.sub-title: Official music video from Red Bull Records
programme.desc: A group of kids are inspired to outrageous shenanigans by a group of bizarro-world Mister Rogers lookalikes. From their album Megalithic Symphony, AWOLNATION dresses up as a group of foul-mouthed, bizarro-world Mister Rogers lookalikes called The Milkmen and inspires a group of '60s children to rock-and-roll shenanigans.

programme.title: B-Boys on the Road
programme.desc: Break'n Reality S1E2. Roxrite attends a BC One All-Stars workshop and makes a big decision about his immediate future. Lilou travels from France to visit his extended family in Algeria. Neguin heads home to Brazil but still struggles with his brother's death last year.

programme.title: Viking Velocity
programme.desc: Downhill racer Erik Lundberg has a gravity-fuelled dream to break the world skateboard speed record. To break the current world speed record on a skateboard, downhill racer Erik Lundberg will have to go faster than 129.95kph (80.7mph). It's a feat that will make him rethink his motivations, his equipment and his commitment to his goal.

programme.title: Freerunning in India
programme.desc: Ryan visits India for the first time and has some fun learning a new skill — Bollywood dancing. Ryan visits India for the first time and has some fun learning a new skill — Bollywood dancing. After mingling with the locals and jumping from city rooftops, Ryan does some parkour in front of the breathtaking Taj Mahal.

programme.title: Surfing at J-Bay 2019
programme.desc: At J-Bay, South Africa, a selection of visiting and local pros feast on several days' worth of flawless walls. As winter set in at J-Bay, in South Africa, a selection of visiting and local pros feasted on several days' worth of flawless walls at the world's best right-hander.

programme.title: Heading Down Under
programme.desc: Jamie O'Brien and the surf crew kick off the show's final season with the madness that only they can deliver. Jamie O'Brien and the whole crew kick off the show's final season with the madness that only they can deliver. Heading from Hawaii to Australia, the guys take a motorhome all over the coast.

programme.title: Kayaks, barrels and powder mountain
programme.desc: Jamie O’Brien and Poopies get up bright and early to go river surfing. Jamie O’Brien and Poopies get up bright and early to start river surfing. Then Poopies gets a serious dose of powder mountain before he and the crew go chasing barrels on kayaks.
